-- Mechel to Extend 22 Billion Rubles of Loans With Gazprombank
-- B y   E m m a   O ’ B r i e n   a n d   Y u l i y a   F e d o r i n o v a
-- 2012-05-04T18:50:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-04/mechel-to-extend-22-billion-rubles-of-loans-with-gazprombank-1-.html
OAO Mechel (MTL) , Russia’s biggest producer
of steelmaking coal, said it signed agreements with OAO
Gazprombank to extend 22 billion rubles ($739 million) of loans,
according to a statement released today.  This is a new agreement with Gazprombank and is in addition
to the as much as $500 million Mechel’s mining division said on
May 2 it had agreed to borrow from the lender to lengthen the
duration of its debt, Ekaterina Videman, a company spokeswoman,
said today.  The pact announced today lengthens revolving credit lines
opened for Mechel units OAO  Chelyabinsk Metallurgical Plant (CHMK) , OOO
Mechel-Service and OOO Mechel-Energo by three to five years,
according to the statement.  To contact the reporters on this story:
